# Order matters — first match wins. Real files in /public and /dist are served
# before _redirects fires, so these rules only run for paths that don't exist
# on disk. The asset-prefix and SW-name rules fail loud (404) when a hashed
# bundle or service-worker script is missing, instead of silently falling
# through to index.html — that masked a pre-release SW issue where the
# browser's SW update check kept getting HTML where JS was expected.
/sw.js          /index.html  404
/workbox-*.js   /index.html  404
/assets/*       /index.html  404
/*              /index.html  200
